enough to be in a situation

00:46:25.500 --> 00:46:32.510
where you have no choice but to
defend yourself that they will

00:46:32.510 --> 00:46:35.444
teach you the most effective
techniques, which are what

00:46:35.444 --> 00:46:36.860
you would not do
in a martial art.

00:46:36.860 --> 00:46:38.720
A groin shot or
gouging someone's

00:46:38.720 --> 00:46:43.120
eyes, the most violent things,
if it comes to that point.

00:46:43.120 --> 00:46:44.620
I mean, I would say
either run away.

00:46:44.620 --> 00:46:47.200
Or if you are in
such a situation,

00:46:47.200 --> 00:46:51.730
then you have to throw
off all the rules.

00:46:51.730 --> 00:46:52.540
And I don't know.

00:46:52.540 --> 00:46:56.520
Generally, I just think I'm a
big fan of doing martial arts

00:46:56.520 --> 00:46:59.300
for one's own
personal development

00:46:59.300 --> 00:47:02.130
but whatever you're called to.

00:47:02.130 --> 00:47:03.589
If you like jiu-jitsu, cool.

00:47:03.589 --> 00:47:04.630
If you like boxing, cool.

00:47:04.630 --> 00:47:06.820
If you like Kenpo, cool.

00:47:06.820 --> 00:47:09.570
Whatever.

00:47:09.570 --> 00:47:10.790
But I'm not sure.

00:47:10.790 --> 00:47:11.380
I don't know.

00:47:11.380 --> 00:47:13.855
In a self-defense situation,
I would, generally, run away.

00:47:13.855 --> 00:47:15.990
JASON KRUEGER: Yeah,
and I also think you

00:47:15.990 --> 00:47:19.380
can go to great jiu-jitsu
academies and academies that

00:47:19.380 --> 00:47:20.380
are just sport oriented.

00:47:20.380 --> 00:47:21.713
And I've trained at all of them.

00:47:21.713 --> 00:47:23.360
And there's
definitely cases where

00:47:23.360 --> 00:47:25.010
I would say I
would not recommend

00:47:25.010 --> 00:47:27.270
one school for those reasons.

